### Islamic Calendar

Unlike the Gregorian calendar, the Islamic calendar is a lunar calendar not based on the seasons (<htcite0>; <htcite1>).

Among the characteristics relevant to this study, the following stand out (<htcite2>):
- The months have 29 or 30 days;
- The year has 354 or 355 days;
- There are four consecutive months with 30 days;
- There are three consecutive months with 29 days;
- A new month begins whenever a new crescent moon is visible.

#### Weeks

Arabs have also used weeks to group days since the first century of their calendar (the 7th century of the Gregorian calendar) (<htcite3>).

Thus, we can also verify the number of weeks in the months of the Islamic calendar (**Calculations 3 and 4**)
